 :tx/rationale "DEEP PATTERN: Across 29 sessions, the single most consistent friction point is NOT any code deficiency — it is the agent-store impedance mismatch. Every session, I (the LLM) must reconstruct my understanding of the project from scratch. braid seed helps, but seeds are PROJECTIONS of the store — they compress away the reasoning chains, the failed approaches, the 'why not X' decisions. What survives across sessions is WHAT was decided, not HOW or WHY the reasoning unfolded. The harvest captures observations and decisions as datoms. But the missing structure is the REASONING TRAJECTORY — the sequence of hypotheses, evidence evaluations, and inference steps that led from problem to solution. This is the epistemic structure that makes a senior engineer valuable: not what they know, but how they reason about what they don't know."
